full_content.content: Common reasons your Electrolux freezer has a drawer problem
The most common reasons your Electrolux freezer has a drawer problem are broken shelves, damaged door or a dead ice maker assembly.
We can help! Our service technicians have repaired over
Electrolux freezers. We can fix yours no matter where you bought it.
Most common repairs needed to fix an Electrolux freezer

Broken freezer shelves can impede the movement of a freezer drawer in several ways. The shelf serves as a structural support for the items stored on it and contributes to the overall stability of the freezer's interior. When a shelf is broken, it may sag or lose its proper alignment, causing the drawer above or below it to encounter resistance when being pulled out or pushed in. Additionally, fragments or protruding edges from the broken shelf can obstruct the path of the drawer, hindering its smooth movement. This obstruction not only affects the ease of access to items inside the drawer but also poses a risk of further damage to the drawer or other components if force is applied to overcome the resistance.

A drawer problem in your freezer could be caused by a damaged door. The door can hit against a drawer when closing and cause damage. A Sears Home Services Technician can visit your home and examine the door. Sometimes simple door adjustment will fix the drawer problem. The technician will replace the door if adjustments don’t fix the issue.
Why does my freezer have a lot of frost inside?

A drawer problem in the freezer can be caused by a bad ice maker assembly. If the ice maker fails to eject a batch of frozen ice cubes in its mold and then activates the water fill valve to fill the ice mold, the fill water will spill out of the ice mold and leak into the freezer. The leaking water can freeze around a drawer and keep it from opening. Replacing the ice maker assembly will fix this type of drawer problem. When your freezer has a drawer that won't pull out, have a Sears Home Services Technician visit your home and fix the issue.
How to replace an ice maker assembly
What to expect when you experience an Electrolux freezer drawer problem issue
How is the drawer problem fixed?

Correcting most drawer problems usually involves replacing the shelves, door or ice maker assembly. However, there are many potential causes, so a thorough diagnosis is key to fixing the problem. An accurate diagnosis is essential to understanding how much the repair will be.
Sears Home Services recommendations for a freezer drawer problem

When the freezer has a drawer problem it can be for many reasons. To avoid replacing unneeded parts we recommend having a Sears Home Services professional perform diagnostic tests to identify the root cause of the problem. Our technicians are experienced at diagnosing all types of freezer failures.
What to look out for with a freezer drawer problem diagnosis

Diagnosing modern appliances without proper knowledge and training can be difficult. Without using proper diagnostic techniques, fixing your freezer problem will only be achieved through changing parts on a hunch. Appliances, especially in the last 10 years, have become extremely advanced, and many models have electronic parts that are difficult to test. DIY repairs on the latest appliance models are becoming increasingly difficult.

full_content.content: What issues occur with an Electrolux freezer drawer?
Common problems include the drawer not sliding smoothly, failing to close, or difficulty opening. These problems are often caused by debris in the rails or a damaged mounting component.
How can I improve a sticking freezer drawer?
Clean the drawer rails and remove any obstructions. Lightly lubricate the rails with a food-safe lubricant if recommended by the manual.
Does a ripped gasket cause drawer closure issues?
Yes. If the gasket is torn or warped, cold air may leak out, causing ice buildup and drawer resistance. Replacing the gasket typically fixes the seal.
When is a professional needed for an Electrolux freezer drawer problem?
If cleaning and minor gasket replacements don’t solve it, the rail assembly or drawer frame may be damaged. A technician can properly align or replace parts as needed.

full_content.content: How Do Chest Freezers Work?: 2025 Explanation
Learn how chest freezers work and how to troubleshoot common problems.

A freezer bag is a specially designed plastic bag used for the cold storage of food in the freezer, offering protection against freezer burn and preserving the food's freshness and flavor over extended periods.

A freezer compressor is a vital component of a freezer's refrigeration system, functioning as a pump to circulate refrigerant through the system, which cools the interior by absorbing and expelling heat.
What is a Freezer Door Gasket?
A freezer door gasket is a flexible seal that outlines the edge of the freezer door, ensuring an airtight closure to maintain cold temperatures inside and prevent warm air from entering.
What is a Manual Defrost Freezer?
A manual defrost freezer is an appliance that needs to be switched off and allowed to thaw periodically to remove accumulated ice, ensuring efficient operation and storage space maximization.
